# MuseDAM Reskin Workflow

## 1. Trigger Conditions
- Figma link, v0 link, or design request.
- “match our design system”, “apply MuseDAM styles”, or paste of HTML/JSX.

## 2. Standard Workflow

### 2.1 Figma Link Branch
1. Figma Make Phase: convert description/link into single MuseDAM-styled HTML with inline styles + data-component attributes (follow designer guidelines exactly).
2. React Translation: convert HTML to TSX line-by-line.
   - Replace buttons/inputs with `src/components/ui/` components.
   - Icons via 03-musedam-icons.mdc.
   - Colors 100% from globals.css variables.
   - Keep data-component comments.

### 2.2 v0 Link Branch (Special)
1. Take v0 generated TSX directly.
2. Strip all original Tailwind colors and classes.
3. Replace:
   - UI primitives → `src/components/ui/` components
   - Spacing → gap-* only
   - Icons → 03-musedam-icons.mdc
4. Preserve logic (state, onClick, forms).
5. Add `data-component="v0-original"` comment.

## 3. Quality Control
- 100% alignment with 01-musedam-core.mdc and designer guidelines.
- Only gap for layout, no margin, responsive, dark mode ready.